com.flowpowered.math.imaginary

Class Quaterniond

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.flowpowered.math.imaginary.Quaterniond
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Imaginaryd, Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<Quaterniond>

    public class Quaterniond
extends Object
implements Imaginaryd, Comparable<Quaterniond>, Serializable, Cloneable
    Represent a quaternion of the form xi + yj + zk + w. The x, y, z and w components are stored as doubles. This class is immutable.
    See Also:

      • conjugate

        public Quaterniond conjugate()
        Conjugates the quaternion.
        Conjugation of a quaternion a is an operation returning quaternion a' such that a' * a = a * a' = |a|2 where |a|2 is squared length of a.
        Specified by:
        conjugate in interface Imaginaryd
        Returns:
        the conjugated quaternion

      • invert

        public Quaterniond invert()
        Inverts the quaternion.
        Inversion of a quaternion a returns quaternion a-1 = a' / |a|2 where a' is conjugation of a, and |a|2 is squared length of a.
        For any quaternions a, b, c, such that a * b = c equations a-1 * c = b and c * b-1 = a are true.
        Specified by:
        invert in interface Imaginaryd
        Returns:
        the inverted quaternion
